						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone (A. 20) in the museum.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1041.</p>						

						<p>This inscription dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 963, Visha (Vṛisha), Jyēśhṭha, ba. 8, Sunday,</hi> records a grant of land by <hi rend="bold">Boḷḷabbe,</hi> the daughter of <hi rend="bold">Gommarasa,</hi> to a temple constructed by her. The land was given to her to be used for charitable purposes by Gommarasa. The gift was entrusted to <hi rend="bold">Chandraśēkhara-Bhaṭṭāra.</hi> The <hi rend="bold">Sēguṇa</hi> family is mentioned.</p>						

						<p>The details of the date correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1041, May 25, Monday</hi> (not Sunday as stated in the record).</p>						

						</summary>
